### 3.2 Inference Pipeline (Sequence Diagram)

This flowchart illustrates precisely what happens when a user clicks "Run Inference" on the UI.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant F as Frontend (React)
    participant API as Backend (FastAPI)
    participant Cache as Redis
    participant Data as yfinance & Macro
    participant ML as AI Inference Engine
    participant Gate as Signal Gates
    
    F->>API: GET /api/signal/{ticker}?tf={timeframe}
    API->>Cache: Check "signal:v6:{ticker}:{tf}"
    
    alt Cache Hit
        Cache-->>API: Return Cached Result
        API-->>F: Instant JSON Response
    else Cache Miss
        API->>Data: Fetch last ~6mo data & Macro (VIX, SP500)
        Data-->>API: Raw OHLCV Time-Series
        
        API->>ML: Apply Denoising + Scaler
        Note over API, ML: Engineers ~36 features (RSI, Breakout, etc.)
        ML->>ML: Forward Pass (Neural Net)
        ML-->>API: Raw Trajectory (P10, P50, P90)
        
        API->>Gate: Evaluate Heuristics
        Note over Gate: Checks RSI Overbought?, Support Breaks?
        Gate-->>API: Final Action [BUY, SELL, HOLD] & Confidence
        
        API->>API: Interpolate 14-period future paths
        API->>API: Format OHLCV timestamps (String/Unix)
        API->>Cache: Set Expiry (e.g., 5 mins)
        API-->>F: SignalAPIResponse (OHLCV, Forecast, Action, Metrics)
    end
```

